<!--
This EJS file generates the HTML content for the login page.
It includes a form for users to input their username and password to log in, along with a link to sign up for a new account if they don't have one.

Variables:
- urlBase: The base URL of the application.
- redirect: An optional parameter indicating the URL to redirect to after successful login.
- message: An optional message to display to the user, such as an error message.

Dependencies:
- Bootstrap Icons: The icon library used for various icons in the UI.
- global-form.css: The global stylesheet for styling form elements.
- definitions.css: The stylesheet specific to definitions-related content.

Form Elements:
- username: Input field for the username.
- password: Input field for the password.
- submit: Button to submit the login form.

Functionality:
- On form submission, the data is sent to the "/login" endpoint with an optional redirect parameter if provided.
- If there is an error message, it is displayed above the form.
-->
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport"
        content="width=device-width, user-scalable=no, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="<%= urlBase %>/css/global-form.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="<%= urlBase %>/css/definitions.css">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="<%= urlBase %>/favicon.png" />
  <title>Login - WTLibrary</title>
</head>
<body>
    <main>
        <header>
            <img src="<%= urlBase %>/favicon.png">
            <h1><a href="<%= urlBase %>">WTLibrary</a></h1>
        </header>
        <h3>Log in to your account</h3>
        <form action="<%= urlBase %><%= redirect ? "/login?redirect=" + redirect : "/login" %>" method="post">
          <label for="username">Username</label>
          <input id="username" name="username" type="text" autocomplete="username" required/>

          <label for="password">Password</label>
          <input id="password" name="password" type="password" autocomplete="password" required/>

            <p>Don't have an account? <a href="<%= urlBase %>/signup">Sign up</a></p>

          <% if (message) { %>
            <p class="text--error" style="margin-top:0;"><%= message %></p>
          <% } %>
          <input type="submit" value="Log in">
        </form>
    </main>
</body>
</html>
